1dwm
============================
1dwm is a fork of the brilliant dwm by suckless (https://dwm.suckless.org/). The
fork focuses on raw speed when managing windows and tries its best to get out of your way.


Installation
------------
You must install the Xlib header files before building. On Arch Linux, these
packages are libx11 and libxft. Arch users should also install the package freetype2, a font
rasterization library.

Run the following to build and install 1dwm:

	sudo make install


Starting 1dwm
-----------
If you use a display manager, select 1dwm at your login screen.
To start with startx, add the following command to your ~/.xinitrc:

	exec dwm1

